WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.003
Crossing 7 Peaks Alone: The Taiwan Mountains Where 4 Hikers Went Missing

00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:28.862
Petr: climb Malunshan and Baigu 

00:00:29.129 --> 00:00:34.167
This is the story of my attempt to reach all seven peaks of Baigu Mountain above 3000 meters.

00:00:34.467 --> 00:00:37.604
It reminded me why preparation matters in the mountains.

00:00:37.737 --> 00:00:44.477
I hiked this direction for the first time, but I was in this area several times before for searching for missing hikers.

00:00:57.490 --> 00:01:01.327
I started alone from Guguan (谷關) in March 2025.

00:01:01.961 --> 00:01:05.098
The weather was still cold, so I packed extra gear.

00:01:06.332 --> 00:01:09.702
My goal: climb all seven peaks of Baigu in one push.

00:01:10.603 --> 00:01:16.242
Most people take the main trail from the other side, but I chose the harder route and cross whole area.

00:01:16.776 --> 00:01:21.514
Through Malun Mountain (馬崙山), over the Malun Baigu Trail (馬崙白姑步道), and leave on the east side.

00:01:23.616 --> 00:01:26.186
The first section goes through Malunshan Trail (馬崙山步道).

00:01:27.821 --> 00:01:32.559
It's initial 6km warm up with 1200m elevation gain.

00:01:33.059 --> 00:01:35.028
It's maintained but steep.

00:01:35.762 --> 00:01:39.933
On the way you can see some man made ruins and bit of history.

00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:44.304
As I joke: past garbage becomes "artifacts" in the present day.

00:01:57.350 --> 00:01:58.918
I used our Tornado vest pack,

00:01:59.018 --> 00:02:02.355
which we developed with Hanchor for light packing in Taiwan mountains.

00:02:03.189 --> 00:02:07.393
It's up to 32 liters capacity, but enough space for several days.

00:02:08.061 --> 00:02:09.462
The vest fits to the body

00:02:09.629 --> 00:02:12.532
and keeps everything accessible with some smart features

00:02:12.599 --> 00:02:14.934
as shoulder pocket for inReach mini.

00:02:15.301 --> 00:02:17.237
You can find it at www.beast.run.

00:02:23.276 --> 00:02:25.678
This direction is not popular.

00:02:26.146 --> 00:02:27.747
Very long climb on day one,

00:02:27.847 --> 00:02:30.650
dense bamboo sections which are hard to navigate in,

00:02:30.750 --> 00:02:32.785
and no reliable water sources.

00:02:32.952 --> 00:02:35.522
Average hiker cannot finish it in one day.

00:02:52.171 --> 00:02:56.342
Near the top of Malun Mountain (馬崙山), I always remember July 2022.

00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:59.379
A hiker went missing here for over a week.

00:02:59.712 --> 00:03:04.117
I was on a long trip in the mountains before I came down and could join the search.

00:03:04.617 --> 00:03:08.321
I was tired and just wished the search is solved soon.

00:03:08.688 --> 00:03:16.029
Something guided me from the top of Malun which is 2,305 meters high, deep into the creek system.

00:03:17.096 --> 00:03:20.700
Down to Malun River (馬崙溪) at 1,730 meters.

00:03:21.935 --> 00:03:25.038
I found him drowned under a waterfall.

00:03:31.311 --> 00:03:36.316
We'll never know exactly what happened, but most likely he took the wrong direction at the summit.

00:03:36.482 --> 00:03:41.087
Realized his mistake and tried to descend randomly to escape the mountains.

00:03:41.521 --> 00:03:43.223
This is always wrong.

00:04:11.784 --> 00:04:16.356
Today we have GPS devices - smartphone apps with offline maps.

00:04:16.823 --> 00:04:18.725
Too many cases could be avoided.

00:04:19.292 --> 00:04:24.731
Followers from overseas often comment about the importance of paper maps, which I am aware of.

00:04:24.897 --> 00:04:30.603
But in reality, I plan my trip on paper and computer maps, and then use GPS navigation.

00:04:31.037 --> 00:04:37.076
So I carry at least two GPS devices as my GPS watch, phone, or inReach2.

00:04:37.243 --> 00:04:40.380
The mountains don't forgive navigation mistakes.

00:05:08.608 --> 00:05:13.980
The hardest section starts after Malun Mountain - climbing to Baigu Mountain West Peak (白姑大山西峰).

00:05:15.114 --> 00:05:16.516
Recently, volunteers did amazing work here - 

00:05:16.582 --> 00:05:19.886
they installed safety ropes, built rainwater collection points,

00:05:19.952 --> 00:05:22.889
and placed red guide strings through the bamboo.

00:05:23.489 --> 00:05:26.159
Maybe three or four kilometers of string.

00:05:56.222 --> 00:05:58.591
Petr: charge my phone (old electric pole)

00:05:58.891 --> 00:06:04.497
It's hard to imagine how much effort humans spent to access these mountain areas to log trees.

00:06:42.401 --> 00:06:45.471
The scenery was amazing and I was lucky for the weather.

00:06:46.038 --> 00:06:48.107
There was a view to another side of valley

00:06:48.274 --> 00:06:54.413
with Jiuxian Shan (九仙山) and Jilong Shan (基隆山) which are almost 3000 meters and also not easy to reach.

00:06:55.047 --> 00:07:00.420
In this long climb were many rocky sections, which made it quite interesting and also unique for Taiwan.

00:07:06.959 --> 00:07:10.363
In Taiwan most hikes are in deep forest with lack of views,

00:07:10.563 --> 00:07:13.332
but here is pretty, but hard.

00:09:47.787 --> 00:09:51.490
Taiwan has 285 peaks over 3000 meters.

00:09:51.991 --> 00:09:55.127
Most hikers know the famous Baiyue (台灣百岳) - the hundred peaks.

00:09:55.528 --> 00:09:58.364
But there are many more that just few people climb.

00:09:59.065 --> 00:10:02.668
After this trip, I've reached about 240 of them.

00:10:16.949 --> 00:10:19.418
I was prepared for snow or wet bamboo.

00:10:19.885 --> 00:10:23.789
I brought waterproof jacket and pants, and waterproof socks.

00:10:24.056 --> 00:10:28.527
And warm waterproof gloves - Showa 282

00:10:28.828 --> 00:10:31.130
Showa gloves look like you are about to clean toilets,

00:10:31.497 --> 00:10:34.266
but the visage is compensated with functions.

00:10:35.067 --> 00:10:38.971
These gloves come in two versions - 281 without warm layer

00:10:39.238 --> 00:10:41.440
282 with warm layer.

00:10:48.047 --> 00:10:51.584
I use 281, but for winter hikes I bought 282

00:10:51.784 --> 00:10:54.353
which I also used for some winter bike rides.

00:10:54.954 --> 00:10:57.523
This trip, I luckily didn't need them.

00:10:57.857 --> 00:11:01.227
Both are waterproof, breathable, and inexpensive.

00:11:01.661 --> 00:11:03.896
Small tip: my hands aren't huge,

00:11:04.030 --> 00:11:07.867
but L size feels small, so I chose LL size.

00:11:19.645 --> 00:11:21.614
You may wonder why I talk about gloves

00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:23.616
and not about other waterproof gear.

00:11:23.983 --> 00:11:26.619
But reality is that my hands get cold quickly

00:11:26.786 --> 00:11:28.254
and it's hard to warm them,

00:11:28.421 --> 00:11:32.692
especially when everything around you is wet, as often is bamboo in Taiwan.

00:11:36.028 --> 00:11:37.129
Round 2

00:11:37.463 --> 00:11:38.764
The Bamboo Battle

00:11:44.437 --> 00:11:48.674
First, I detoured south to West-South Peak of Baigu Mountain (白姑大山西南峰).

00:11:49.075 --> 00:11:55.014
On the map, just 900 meters, but it took me 1.5 hours in one direction and then back.

00:11:56.282 --> 00:11:59.685
Incredibly dense bamboo, not much marking.

00:12:02.388 --> 00:12:06.892
You may notice my fancy goggles, last what you need here is poked eye.

00:12:07.726 --> 00:12:11.730
I was thinking about the purpose of life while pushing through that bamboo.

00:12:20.239 --> 00:12:23.342
Petr: Oh... West-South Peak. Oh My God this is crazy.

00:12:24.009 --> 00:12:28.114
Petr: That was not easy. 900m and 1.5 hour.

00:12:33.452 --> 00:12:35.888
(Just checking little bit behind peak)

00:12:50.402 --> 00:12:53.105
(I let water here. And lost my trekking pole.)

00:12:59.378 --> 00:13:00.946
Petr:  So cool here.

00:13:19.365 --> 00:13:21.634
I continued to Baigu Mountain Three-Forked Peak (白姑大山三叉峰),

00:13:21.967 --> 00:13:25.037
and finally reached the main trail (白姑大山徑) from the other side.

00:13:30.075 --> 00:13:34.780
Petr: YES. Crazy, 11 hours.

00:13:36.215 --> 00:13:37.817
This leads to the main peak.

00:13:37.983 --> 00:13:42.321
I was prepared for snow or wet bamboo, but the weather was perfect.

00:13:42.755 --> 00:13:45.357
Clear sky, but it was getting late.

00:13:45.825 --> 00:13:48.761
I decided to sleep on top of Baigu Mountain (白姑大山).

00:13:55.734 --> 00:14:02.908
Day one: 19 kilometers, 3,250 meters elevation gain, over 11.5 hours.

00:14:03.676 --> 00:14:06.779
Most hikers cannot complete this direction in one day.

00:14:07.313 --> 00:14:11.850
I carried all my water from Guguan (谷關) and still had enough for the night and morning.

00:14:12.985 --> 00:14:15.988
Petr: Bai Gu Da Shan 白姑大山

00:14:20.826 --> 00:14:23.963
I don't recommend sleeping on top of mountain or open space.

00:14:24.063 --> 00:14:26.899
It's always better to sleep under some vegetation.

00:14:27.333 --> 00:14:32.805
But if you do, you have to have good weather and know what to do if something is turning wrong.

00:14:35.207 --> 00:14:40.679
I don't like spending money on gear I don't need, but years ago I invested in good sleep gear.

00:14:41.213 --> 00:14:46.852
Good 20F down sleeping bag, short inflatable mat, quality bivy and tarp.

00:14:47.319 --> 00:14:51.056
My whole sleep system weighs under 1,200 grams.

00:14:59.265 --> 00:15:01.533
Sleeping under tarp is not for everyone,

00:15:01.834 --> 00:15:06.272
but it's one way to shave weight of sleeping gear and it has also benefits.

00:15:06.805 --> 00:15:09.541
But for tonight I even didn't build the tarp.

00:15:09.908 --> 00:15:13.045
It's really important to have good sleep if possible.

00:15:15.014 --> 00:15:18.450
The night was so peaceful and surprisingly not windy.

00:15:20.286 --> 00:15:21.687
I slept well.

00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:34.099
I woke up not so early because I wanted to enjoy sunrise on top of Baigu (白姑大山).

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:36.235
It was stunning.

00:15:36.335 --> 00:15:39.238
After packing, I continued down the main trail

00:15:39.405 --> 00:15:42.775
steep descent with rock ravine at the bottom.

00:15:43.575 --> 00:15:47.546
In the end of 2020, one hiker went ahead of his group.

00:15:47.947 --> 00:15:50.582
At the ravine, instead of turning right,

00:15:50.716 --> 00:15:54.753
he continued left down into the stones and to the creek.

00:15:55.721 --> 00:16:01.060
SAR units searched for him - they found an SOS label made from stones down in the creek,

00:16:01.260 --> 00:16:03.729
just before a high waterfall.

00:16:04.229 --> 00:16:06.265
But the hiker was never found.

00:16:08.701 --> 00:16:11.537
I personally didn't join many searching missions that time

00:16:11.704 --> 00:16:13.939
and the case was complicated with snow.

00:16:37.529 --> 00:16:41.667
I just realized back in July 2020 when I was still young and fast,

00:16:41.834 --> 00:16:46.271
I did fast ascent and descent on main course in 5 hours 15 minutes.

00:17:01.053 --> 00:17:03.155
These are new reflective markers,

00:17:03.322 --> 00:17:06.025
added to the main trail after the incidents.

00:17:06.325 --> 00:17:09.561
It reminds me of another SAR story from 2021.

00:17:10.329 --> 00:17:15.467
I found a missing senior hiker very deep in a creek near Sanzui Mountain (三錐山).

00:17:16.969 --> 00:17:18.470
(sound of helicopter)

00:17:18.570 --> 00:17:22.107
Another case of someone getting lost from their group.

00:17:22.441 --> 00:17:26.178
It always reminds me: whether you go alone or in a group,

00:17:26.345 --> 00:17:30.215
each member should be prepared and should know how to navigate alone.

00:17:31.383 --> 00:17:35.154
It's very easy for less experienced hikers to get lost from the group.

00:17:35.387 --> 00:17:36.955
Not always the slowest person,

00:17:37.122 --> 00:17:40.459
sometimes even fit hikers go ahead and get lost.

00:17:41.560 --> 00:17:44.563
Petr: I found him. I was almost going back.

00:17:45.497 --> 00:17:46.765
Petr: Mr. Huang

00:17:47.132 --> 00:17:50.335
Sorry... Sorry...

00:17:51.069 --> 00:17:53.238
This was my first time finding a dead hiker alone

00:17:53.372 --> 00:17:55.441
and it was very tough terrain.

00:17:56.008 --> 00:17:57.810
It's always shocking.

00:17:59.445 --> 00:18:01.079
Petr : I don't understand how he got here.

00:18:01.814 --> 00:18:04.550
Petr: I have so much difficulty go here.

00:18:04.817 --> 00:18:08.487
Since then, during my solo searches, I've found many more,

00:18:08.720 --> 00:18:10.656
unfortunately many deaths.

00:18:11.323 --> 00:18:13.092
Petr: Never Go Down!

00:18:13.258 --> 00:18:16.662
But what's worse - some missing were never found.

00:18:18.163 --> 00:18:23.936
I continued over Baigu Southeast Peak (白姑東南峰) to the grassland with black pools Siyan Chi campsite (司晏池營地).

00:18:24.670 --> 00:18:28.373
I was out of water and needed water for today and tonight.

00:18:29.274 --> 00:18:30.776
The next section would be hard,

00:18:31.009 --> 00:18:33.879
and I wasn't sure I could finish before dark.

00:18:37.749 --> 00:18:42.121
I use a Sawyer filter and two water bags - Evernew 2-liter bags (EVERNEW 水袋 2L).

00:18:42.654 --> 00:18:45.290
One for dirty water, one for clean.

00:18:45.891 --> 00:18:49.561
The trick: use an adapter screw to coupling filter with bags,

00:18:49.695 --> 00:18:53.065
and set up gravitational filtering instead of squeezing.

00:18:53.365 --> 00:18:57.736
Hang it and let gravity work - very dirty water becomes relatively clean.

00:18:58.036 --> 00:19:00.038
Drinkable without boiling.

00:19:00.639 --> 00:19:04.943
At least I had not any stomach difficulties due to drinking bad water.

00:19:09.915 --> 00:19:14.486
I continued straight into dense bamboo toward my sixth and seventh peaks.

00:19:14.653 --> 00:19:19.057
Baigu Mountain Middle Peak (白姑大山中峰) and far one - Baigu Mountain East Peak (白姑大山東峰).

00:19:21.527 --> 00:19:24.530
Petr:  This considred to be highway.

00:19:28.734 --> 00:19:32.738
There was even an open area, quite pretty with fine black pool.

00:19:36.408 --> 00:19:39.811
Black pool water is really dirty and can clog filters badly.

00:19:40.145 --> 00:19:46.752
I tried various filters - Katadyn BeFree is useless for high mountain trips in Taiwan, it clogs terribly.

00:19:47.252 --> 00:19:49.288
I tried smaller Sawyer versions too,

00:19:49.454 --> 00:19:53.659
but the best is their biggest classic filter - SP129.

00:19:53.992 --> 00:19:58.497
Just remember to flush it in reverse with clean water after each trip.

00:19:59.198 --> 00:20:04.102
And don't let your filter freeze - put it in your sleeping bag during winter nights.

00:20:09.441 --> 00:20:14.179
Same with electronics - keep your phone and any batteries in your sleeping bag too.

00:20:14.846 --> 00:20:17.082
Your phone doesn't need to be off for the night,

00:20:17.216 --> 00:20:20.219
but put it in airplane mode to preserve the battery.

00:20:25.924 --> 00:20:29.995
I reached Baigu Mountain Middle Peak (白姑大山中峰) - not as bad as expected.

00:20:31.830 --> 00:20:37.803
But reaching the farthest peak - Baigu Mountain East Peak (白姑大山東峰) - was tough, the bamboo got dense.

00:20:38.270 --> 00:20:42.708
When I finally reached it, my mission of completing all seven peaks was over.

00:20:44.076 --> 00:20:45.978
Haha, not really.

00:20:47.212 --> 00:20:50.315
My plan: continue on the east ridge if weather allows,

00:20:50.515 --> 00:20:53.385
if weather turned bad, return to main trail.

00:20:53.719 --> 00:20:57.289
The weather was perfect that day, so I continued northeast.

00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:02.861
After a while, I started regretting it.

00:21:03.929 --> 00:21:08.433
I was descending a very steep slope and had to stop and rethink.

00:21:08.667 --> 00:21:11.837
Was it worth returning back and leaving mountains by common trail

00:21:12.137 --> 00:21:15.140
and stopping some car back to Puli for dinner with family?

00:21:15.474 --> 00:21:16.775
Or keep going?

00:21:17.175 --> 00:21:19.444
I decided to keep going.

00:21:28.387 --> 00:21:31.823
The bamboo changed to a narrow ridge with bad landslide.

00:21:31.990 --> 00:21:34.926
If I had an accident here, nobody could help me.

00:21:51.543 --> 00:21:54.012
On a small peak, I saw traces.

00:21:54.146 --> 00:21:56.715
The group probably cut bamboo to camp here.

00:21:57.949 --> 00:21:59.818
I cannot imagine spending the night here.

00:21:59.918 --> 00:22:02.354
Definitely not alone, not today.

00:22:04.923 --> 00:22:08.527
No trail, no marking, no obvious direction,

00:22:08.627 --> 00:22:10.829
no hope, just fear.

00:22:11.363 --> 00:22:14.700
Everywhere, finger-thick bamboo, hard to push through.

00:22:15.334 --> 00:22:17.969
I had GPS tracks from a recent group which went over,

00:22:18.270 --> 00:22:21.073
but there was no way to recognize where I should crawl.

00:22:22.274 --> 00:22:24.142
I was heading toward Dong Gao Mountain (東高山)

00:22:24.276 --> 00:22:26.178
also called Ta Ban Mountain (塔班山).

00:22:26.445 --> 00:22:28.080
It was so hard.

00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:32.084
Here you understand how important GPS navigation is.

00:22:32.184 --> 00:22:34.820
You cannot determine direction clearly.

00:22:35.520 --> 00:22:38.890
Even with paper map and compass, the scale isn't enough,

00:22:39.091 --> 00:22:42.361
it's very easy to take the wrong direction in dense bamboo.

00:22:43.962 --> 00:22:47.566
I was prepared for this, but it was harder than expected.

00:22:48.100 --> 00:22:50.902
Lucky for me, the weather was perfect.

00:22:52.170 --> 00:22:55.173
Petr: For little bit no bamboo.

00:23:05.817 --> 00:23:08.086
(kicking old rusty can)

00:23:10.689 --> 00:23:14.926
Some sections were pretty - open space or nice forest without bamboo.

00:23:15.994 --> 00:23:17.496
And some places were ugly.

00:23:17.796 --> 00:23:20.065
I could see a lot of old trash from workers

00:23:20.165 --> 00:23:22.501
who logged forest here in the past.

00:23:23.602 --> 00:23:27.572
The logging was stopped and mountain rats (山老鼠) activity is also controlled now,

00:23:27.906 --> 00:23:30.675
so all this trash and gear is quite old.

00:23:34.713 --> 00:23:37.415
I think the main hiking trail to Baigu is quite new.

00:23:38.283 --> 00:23:42.421
From old maps, I have a feeling the original entry to mountains was this direction.

00:23:42.654 --> 00:23:48.560
In past they didn't care about peaks but cared about access to forest areas for trees.

00:23:50.429 --> 00:23:52.697
From Baigu East Peak (白姑大山東峰) to Dong Gao Mountain (東高山):

00:23:52.798 --> 00:23:55.100
just 3.3 kilometers on the map.

00:23:55.500 --> 00:23:58.003
It took forever and took so much energy,

00:23:58.236 --> 00:24:00.906
but I finally reached the peak.

00:24:02.741 --> 00:24:05.744
Petr: So tired.

00:24:07.546 --> 00:24:12.117
I didn't celebrate long and detoured to one big pool - Ta Ban Chi (塔班池).

00:24:12.484 --> 00:24:14.252
Also possible to camp there.

00:24:14.886 --> 00:24:19.558
Just the right time to get water, I took a moment to rest and cook tea.

00:24:24.196 --> 00:24:29.801
From here, basically just five kilometers of descent toward the industrial road - Sheng Li Road (勝利路).

00:24:30.268 --> 00:24:33.538
Should be easier, but it was still not easy.

00:24:34.039 --> 00:24:36.007
I trusted the GPS in my Garmin watch

00:24:36.107 --> 00:24:40.378
and kept going through bamboo but also along edge of deep cliff.

00:24:41.046 --> 00:24:44.883
On some views I could see in far my final destination,

00:24:45.050 --> 00:24:47.219
village of my wife Lixing (力行).

00:24:55.794 --> 00:24:59.130
Petr: Please No More Bamboo. No More Bamboo!

00:25:03.802 --> 00:25:05.837
Petr: Paolyta-B 保力達B

00:25:13.178 --> 00:25:17.382
Another "famous case" - university student Zhang Bowei (張博崴).

00:25:18.250 --> 00:25:23.188
Found after 51 days in 2011, unfortunately dead.

00:25:23.989 --> 00:25:27.526
But evidence showed he survived many days after injury.

00:25:28.226 --> 00:25:31.630
This case raised many voices about SAR efficiency in Taiwan.

00:25:32.197 --> 00:25:34.833
SAR is not perfect and never will be perfect,

00:25:35.567 --> 00:25:39.471
but in mountains, safety first depends on the hiker themselves.

00:25:39.838 --> 00:25:42.307
Then on assistance if really needed.

00:25:48.914 --> 00:25:51.216
The lesson: If you really get lost

00:25:51.316 --> 00:25:53.652
you cannot leave mountains in random directions.

00:25:53.818 --> 00:25:56.788
It often leads to difficult creeks with waterfalls.

00:25:58.957 --> 00:26:03.194
All four cases had this in similar, they kept going down in random direction

00:26:03.361 --> 00:26:05.430
and ended injured in creek.

00:26:05.564 --> 00:26:06.464
Died.

00:26:07.165 --> 00:26:11.002
GPS navigation is so important to me as well as gear choice.

00:26:14.839 --> 00:26:16.074
Petr: Work house

00:26:18.443 --> 00:26:23.315
It's important to note - none of them were attempting this difficult route.

00:26:23.715 --> 00:26:26.017
They were all on the standard trail.

00:26:39.998 --> 00:26:43.868
I finally reached Sheng Li Road (勝利路), real relief.

00:26:44.336 --> 00:26:46.538
Just over one hour to sunset.

00:26:46.805 --> 00:26:49.741
I was on this road earlier this year with my gravel bike,

00:26:49.941 --> 00:26:52.811
also a two-day trip, so I'm familiar with it.

00:26:53.878 --> 00:26:57.649
My plan: reach the main road, still ten kilometers away.

00:26:58.049 --> 00:27:00.919
From calculation, not possible before dark.

00:27:03.855 --> 00:27:05.790
Petr: Finally... Finally...

00:27:06.558 --> 00:27:08.093
Petr: Oh My God

00:27:08.626 --> 00:27:10.228
Petr: 11 hours

00:27:10.729 --> 00:27:13.198
Petr: Now 10km walk. At least 10km walk (will be 22km)

00:27:13.898 --> 00:27:19.404
This is the benefit of light packing - even in winter, my base weight is just five kilograms.

00:27:19.771 --> 00:27:22.073
I could walk fast, even jog.

00:27:22.374 --> 00:27:25.610
But I had a feeling I wouldn't be able to stop any car

00:27:25.777 --> 00:27:28.113
or truck to my final destination:

00:27:28.380 --> 00:27:34.052
Lixing village (力行) - also called Marepa (馬烈霸) - still 12 kilometers more.

00:27:34.219 --> 00:27:36.287
I remember there was a local store,

00:27:36.421 --> 00:27:41.426
I bought snack and beer and decided to just walk to Lixing in the dark.

00:27:41.993 --> 00:27:45.730
It was actually quite nice and I little bit miss endurance sport

00:27:45.930 --> 00:27:49.768
and the feeling when you are tired but getting closer to finish.

00:27:49.934 --> 00:27:52.937
Petr: This is how they reinforce the roads here. (Czech language)

00:27:53.571 --> 00:27:58.076
That day: 40 kilometers in my legs, fifteen hours of moving.

00:27:59.511 --> 00:28:04.049
Marepa (馬烈霸) is my wife's father's village, I would stay in our house there.

00:28:04.516 --> 00:28:08.553
Before the village, I visited my father-in-law at the cemetery.

00:28:09.020 --> 00:28:12.323
The grave is far in the corner behind bushes.

00:28:12.590 --> 00:28:18.196
I promised we would visit him again in April, tomb-sweeping day with the whole family.

00:28:18.730 --> 00:28:21.066
I slept in our old village house very well.

00:28:21.666 --> 00:28:24.402
Next day, I caught a ride back to Puli.

00:28:24.569 --> 00:28:27.105
The driver could be hired by McLaren racing team.

00:28:27.505 --> 00:28:31.209
Got back to Puli by noon to have lunch with my family.

00:28:31.810 --> 00:28:35.246
A couple days later, I biked back to Guguan (谷關) for my car.

00:28:35.513 --> 00:28:38.583
I really missed hiking, this kind of adventure.

00:28:38.983 --> 00:28:42.921
But it reminds me: preparation before any mountain trip matters,

00:28:43.154 --> 00:28:44.556
and choosing the right gear,

00:28:44.689 --> 00:28:47.659
and choosing the right partner if you go with group.

00:28:48.026 --> 00:28:51.730
The mountains are always there, but we have to be prepared for them.

